article.headline: UCF 70, Penn St. 59
article.story: LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. (AP) -- Jermaine Taylor scored 23 points and Mike O'Donnell had 16, leading Central Florida to a 70-59 victory against Penn State in the seventh-place game of the Old Spice Classic on Sunday. Geary Claxton scored 22 points and Jamelle Cornley finished with 11 to pace Penn State (2-3), which has three November losses for the first time since 1978. Central Florida (3-2) outscored Penn State 18-4 from the free-throw line en route to its first victory in seven attempts all-time against Big 10 opponents. The Nittany Lions built an eight-point lead midway through the first half, but a pair of 3-pointers each by Taylor and O'Donnell helped the Knights take a 32-24 advantage into the break. Central Florida hit four-of-seven shots from long range in the first half. Penn State made only three-of-17 from behind the arc before the intermission and five-of-31 overall. UCF extended its lead to 11 points early in the second half, but Claxton scored seven points in a 9-0 run that trimmed the deficit to 37-35. Penn State never drew any closer as UCF pulled away. The Old Spice Classic was being held at Walt Disney World.
